data.name: CON_found_damagecfg
data.value: Found a config file for damage dump plugin, parsing

data.name: CON_InvaildPSO2_binPath
data.value:
Please select your pso2_bin directory. OverParse uses this to read your damage logs.
If you picked a folder while setting up the Tweaker, choose that. Otherwise, it will be in your PSO2 installation folder.

data.name: CON_Update_first
data.value: FIRST ATTACK RECORDED: {0} dmg from {1} ({2}) with {3}, to {4} ({5})

data.name: UI_AskTweakerUsage
data.value: Do you use the PSO2 Tweaker?

data.name: UI_CanceledDirPicker
data.value: OverParse needs a valid PSO2 installation to function. The application will now close.

data.name: UI_Hack
data.value:
Your PSO2 folder doesn't contain any damagelogs. This is not an error, just a reminder!
Please turn on the Damage Parser plugin in PSO2 Tweaker (orb menu > Plugins). OverParse needs this to function. You may also want to update the plugins while you're there.

data.name: UI_InvaildPSO2_binPath
data.value:
Please select your pso2_bin directory.
This folder will be inside your PSO2 install folder, which is usually at C:\PHANTASYSTARONLINE2\.
If you installed the game multiple times (e.g. through the torrent), please make sure you pick the right one, or OverParse won't be able to read your logs!

data.name: UI_Plugin_Prompt_denied
data.value:
OverParse needs the Damage Parser plugin to function.
The application will now close.

data.name: UI_Plugin_Prompt_initial
data.value:
OverParse needs a Tweaker plugin to recieve its damage information.
The plugin can be installed without the Tweaker, but it won't be automatically updated, and I can't provide support for this method.
Do you want to try to manually install the Damage Parser plugin?

data.name: UI_Plugin_Prompt_update
data.value:
This release of OverParse includes a new version of the parsing plugin. Would you like to update now?
OverParse may behave unpredictably if you use a different version than it expects.

data.name: UI_SelectPSO2_Finder
data.value: Select your pso2_bin folder. This will be inside the folder you installed PSO2 to.

data.name: UI_UpdatePlugin_Bad
data.value:
Something went wrong with manual installation. This usually means that the files are already in use: try again with PSO2 closed.
If you've recieved this message even after closing PSO2, you may need to run OverParse as administrator.

data.name: UI_UpdatePlugin_Good
data.value: Setup complete! A few files have been copied to your pso2_bin folder.\n\nIf PSO2 is running right now, you'll need to close it before the changes can take effect.

data.name: UI_InvaildPSO2_binPath_NAG
data.value:
That doesn't appear to be a valid pso2_bin directory.
If you installed the game using default settings, it will probably be in C:\PHANTASYSTARONLINE2\pso2_bin\. Otherwise, find the location you installed to.
